<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I just have to say something...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Malark">Malark</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:57 a.m. 1/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I just have to say something...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2113" TARGET=_self>Re: Pk balancing for wizard types</A> (Mieth)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>In that playing around in the Qeynos Hills/BlackBurrow/EverFrost/Qeynos areas, is that ROOT seems to be the primary cause of death for anyone. I dislike going to Qeynos because of the sheer number of people that think they can simply get a druid or wizard to level 4, then kill all the newbies for the "loads of money they will be carrying". The usual set of events is the guy tries to ROOT, if it fails he tries again or runs. If he starts getting hit, he runs. If the ROOT takes, thens its full burn time. I know since I starte recently I'm only seeing the first dozen levels (and that's where PKing is at its greatest), but it really burns me when I see a bunch of Knights of Terror camping and just killing anyone they see, and that their primary weapon is Root (SOP is to have two or three casters Root at same time, then burn down), or even see lone casters Rooting people.

<BR>Of course in all this whining I don't have a solution, there really isn't a good one. Wizards were designed to be made for battle (and in higher levels transport), so naturally they should probably be superior to many of the other classes. The only recourse is to group up and beat the wizard/druid/whoever down. Unfortunately in the lower levels most people are interested in killing each other instead of grouping up. In fact, I think that if Root didn't exist, there'd probably be a lot of running battles if any at all. Most people don't like losing stuff, so they run. No good answer, but wizards in my experience or obviously not getting the shaft in PvP. Whether they dominate or not I'm not totally sure, but they do play a major role in PvP combat (or I guess from my experience, PK combat)
<P>Malark
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
